com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.embedded.client

Class EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterQueuedListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.CatalysServerLifecycleListenerAdapter
      • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.embedded.client.EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterQueuedListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFIXListenerCallback, IFIXListenerProviderCallback, IStatefulFIXListenerCallback, ICatalysServerLifecycleListener, Runnable

    public final class EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterQueuedListener
extends CatalysServerLifecycleListenerAdapter
implements IStatefulFIXListenerCallback, IFIXListenerProviderCallback, ICatalysServerLifecycleListener, Runnable
    Sample application which acts as an in process adapter client and processes events and messages passively (i.e. queues events/messages for subsequent processing in another thread).

    When we receive inbound messages callbacks (via IFIXListenerCallback) we queue them for subsequent processing in another thread. This is only recommended if the application is not capable of processing messages as quickly as they are delivered.

    We use a separate thread for consuming inbound events and messages. This thread simply polls the queue and logs inbound messages.

    In order to demonstrate sending FIX messages we use an EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterSender which runs a separate sending thread. We choose to maintain a reference to the IFIXSourceProxy as we know there is only one of them. An alternate technique is to use the EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter.send(String, IFIXMessage) method which looks up the required proxy by ID on the fly.

    The techniques used here represent one possibility for processing events and messages passively, while still being reasonably efficient. There are other options with respect to serialization and persistence (including whether persistence is required at all). Please consider your requires before simply using this code.

    Disclaimer: This is example code only and is not intended for production use.

    See Also:
    EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterUnqueuedListener

      • storesMessages

        public boolean storesMessages()
        Description copied from interface: IStatefulFIXListenerCallback
        Return whether the specified listener expects to store messages or not.

        This method is invoked once at the time the listener is first installed.

        The return value is used by the framework to decide whether to send reused messages (for a given session) to the listener or not. If the listener expects a new message object instance each time it should return true, otherwise the framework attempts to send the same message object instance each time.

        Specified by:
        storesMessages in interface IStatefulFIXListenerCallback
        Returns:
        True if the listener expects/requires a new object instance each time, false otherwise.
